Turkish, Russian Tourists Help Boost Greek Visitor Numbers 13%

-- B y   E l e n i   C h r e p a
-- 
2011-07-20T13:02:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/turkish-russian-tourists-help-boost-greek-visitor-numbers-13-.html
The number of visitors to  Greece 
increased 13 percent during the first three months of 2011, as
arrivals from Turkey and Russia almost doubled, according to
 data  from the  Hellenic Statistical Authority .  The number of visitors from Turkey surged 98 percent to
84,559, compared with the first quarter of 2010, while Russian
arrivals increased 80 percent to 12,440. The largest number of
arrivals came from  Bulgaria , with 113,992, up 27 percent.  A total of 1,108,387 million people arrived in Greece from
January to March, up from 980,411 in the same period of 2010.
Visitors from Europe, which account for more than 80 percent of
total arrivals, increased 8.6 percent to 905,887.  Tourism contributes 16 percent to Greek gross domestic
product and accounts for one in five jobs, according to the
 World Travel and Tourism Council , an industry group.  -- Editor: Peter Branton  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eleni Chrepa in Athens at 
